## Early game

**Hellas** on Mars (Extermination) is a quick way to stock up on Morphics
from the very start of the star chart — the wiki notes Morphics have a much
higher drop chance on Mars than anywhere else, "making it one of the easiest
rare components to obtain" there despite the rare-resource label. Morphics
have no enemy drop table, so this comes from the mission's resource caches
rather than kill speed. **Lares** on Mercury (Defense) is a fine secondary
stop if you're farming before Mars is unlocked.

## Mid & late game

Mars stays the best Morphics planet at every progression stage, per the
wiki, so **Olympus** (Disruption, Steel Path) is the natural endgame upgrade:
a Steel Path squad gets more Disruption rotations completed per hour than
short missions elsewhere. Morphics are still cache-based rather than an
enemy drop, so Resource Drop Boosters and the Steel Path passive don't change
the per-cache odds — running more rotations is what raises the yield.

